    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="876"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1159</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1043</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-23">May 23,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received May 28.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my telegram No. 26, May 23, 4 p.m.,
                        1940.<note n="44" xml:id="d876fn44">Not printed; it stated that the Honduran
                        Government received on May 23 similar protest from the German Government, a
                        copy of which Minister Erwin was sending to the Department by air mail
                        (740.00111 A.R./1133).</note> I received in confidence from the Honduran
                    Foreign Office today through Señor don Fernando Lardizabal, Chief of Protocol,
                    the copy of memorandum <pb facs="0806" n="794" xml:id="pg_794"/> submitted to
                    the Honduran Government by the German Minister in Guatemala, which, together
                    with a translation thereof are made enclosures to this despatch.<note n="45"
                        xml:id="d876fn45">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The reply of the Honduran Government has not at this hour been formulated and,
                    therefore, I am not able to state its contents. It will probably be several days
                    before an answer is ready for delivery, as the Foreign Minister<note n="46"
                        xml:id="d876fn46">Salvador Aguirre.</note> must confer with President Carías
                    before anything is done. However, my information is that the response will
                    decline to give any satisfaction to this protest.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John D. Erwin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
